 (3441,'Galileo',NULL,4090,'Galileo&#039;s Compass','Galileo&#039;s compass looks like the compasses that we all know from school.  In reality it has a profoundly different meaning: it is an extraordinary instrument that can perform various types of calculations and find the solution to various types of problems.  The principle on which it is based is very simple: it is a proportional mechanism; given the proportion between A and B, one can apply the same proportion to another quantity.  The compass has various applications, particularly in the military field.  Galileo&#039;s instrument became very popular also for the brilliant way with which Galileo managed to promote it and also transform it &hellip; in a income instrument!\r\n',1),
