 (4443,'Journey&#039;s End',4431,5250,'Journey&#039;s End','In a final attempt to organize the expedition, Slick called in Peter Byrne, a big-game hunter of tiger and elephant, who had worked with him on previous hunts in the Himalayas.  This did not produce the desired effect but added another personality to an already fractured group.  As a result, the expedition ended in 1960, its main claim to fame not being the 15 footprints that it claimed to have seen but the conflicts that it established among those working in field research. ',4),
